# Sprint 0: Project Scaffold & Base Layout

## Prerequisites

Before the agent begins, the following must be true on the machine:
- Node.js 20+ installed (`node --version` must show v20.x or higher)
- npm available
- Working directory is the empty project folder (the agent does not create or manage a git repo — git is handled separately by the human)

## UX Flows

1. [Any page]: User opens site → browser loads HTsprints/sprint-00-scaffold.todo sprints/sprint-01-homepage.todo sprints/sprint-02-sanglogium.todo sprints/sprint-03-pages.todo sprints/sprint-04-deploy.todoML shell → sees consistent nav and footer on every page → can click nav links to other pages
2. [Dev workflow]: Developer installs dependencies → project builds without errors → dev server starts

