sprints/sprint-00-scaffold.todo sprints/sprint-01-homepage.todo sprints/sprint-02-sanglogium.todo sprints/sprint-03-pages.todo sprints/sprint-04-deploy.todo
A working Astro 5 + Tailwind CSS 3 project with a reusable base layout, zero-JS navigation, static footer, and placeholder assets in place. Every page renders with the same HTML shell, system font stack, and global styles. Nav links work between all planned routes.

## Architecture Contract

- **Framework**: Astro 5, `output: 'static'`
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 3 via `@astrojs/tailwind` integration; `@tailwind` directives in `src/styles/global.css`
- **Fonts**: System font stack only (`system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif`) — zero web font requests
- **Navigation**: Static Astro component, CSS hover states only, zero JS; active state is out of scope
- **Routing**: File-based Astro routing (`src/pages/*.astro`); `trailingSlash: 'always'` set in config
- **Client-side transitions**: `<ClientRouter />` in base layout for SPA-like navigation

### File contracts

- `astro.config.mjs` — must contain: `output: 'static'`, `site: 'https://munrhalls.com'`, `trailingSlash: 'always'`, `@astrojs/tailwind` integration
- `src/layouts/Base.astro` — HTML shell: `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<head>` with meta tags (title, description, OG tags), `<ClientRouter />`, nav slot, main slot, footer slot; accepts `title` and `description` props for per-page OG customization
- `src/components/Nav.astro` — `<nav>` with 4 `<a>` links: About (`/about/`), Projects (`/projects/`), Skills (`/skills/`), Contact (`/contact/`); CSS hover underline/color change; no JS; no active state
- `src/components/Footer.astro` — `<footer>` with static copyright text
- `src/styles/global.css` — `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;` + `body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; }` + `html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }`
- `src/pages/index.astro` — placeholder page using Base layout (replaced fully in Sprint 1)
- `src/pages/about.astro` — placeholder page using Base layout (replaced in Sprint 3)
- `src/pages/projects.astro` — placeholder page using Base layout (replaced in Sprint 3)
- `src/pages/projects/sanglogium.astro` — placeholder page using Base layout (replaced in Sprint 2)
- `src/pages/skills.astro` — placeholder page using Base layout (replaced in Sprint 3)
- `src/pages/contact.astro` — placeholder page using Base layout (replaced in Sprint 3)
- `src/pages/404.astro` — simple "Page not found" page using Base layout; `export const prerender = true`
- `src/assets/images/sanglogium/` — 12 placeholder PNGs (800×600, solid `#e2e2e2` fill)
- `src/assets/images/sanglogium/architecture-diagram.svg` — placeholder SVG (rectangle with label "Architecture Diagram")
- `src/assets/images/sanglogium/images-pipeline-diagram.svg` — placeholder SVG (rectangle with label "Image Pipeline Diagram")
- `public/resume.pdf` — placeholder: empty text file renamed to resume.pdf
- `public/favicon.svg` — simple SVG favicon: dark square (`#080808`) with a small white diamond shape centered; viewBox="0 0 32 32"

### OG meta tag spec (Base.astro `<head>`)

```html
<meta property="og:title" content={title} />
<meta property="og:description" content={description} />
<meta property="og:type" content="website" />
<meta property="og:url" content={Astro.url} />
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
<meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
<meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
```

`Base.astro` accepts a `description` prop (string) alongside `title`. Default description: `"Full-stack developer portfolio — munrhalls.com"`.

### Tailwind installation (exact commands)

```bash
npm create astro@latest . -- --template minimal --no-install --no-git
npm install
npx astro add tailwind
```

When `npx astro add tailwind` prompts, accept all defaults. This installs `@astrojs/tailwind` and Tailwind CSS 3. Do not install Tailwind 4 or `@tailwindcss/vite`.

## Scope Contracts

### Scope Contract 1: Astro + Tailwind Scaffold

**UX Slice**
- Developer runs setup commands → project initializes → no build errors

**Architecture Slice**
- Run the exact install commands from the Architecture Contract above
- Verify `astro dev` starts without errors
- Verify `astro build` completes without errors

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] `npm run dev` starts on expected port with no errors
- [ ] Opening `localhost` shows a page (no build crash)
- [ ] Tailwind classes apply (test with a `bg-red-500` class on a div, confirm red background)
- [ ] `astro.config.mjs` contains `output: 'static'`, `site: 'https://munrhalls.com'`, `trailingSlash: 'always'`

---

### Scope Contract 2: Placeholder Assets

**UX Slice**
- Image and file references in code resolve without 404s during development

**Architecture Slice**
- Create `src/assets/images/sanglogium/` directory
- Generate 12 placeholder PNGs programmatically: 800×600 solid `#e2e2e2` — use a Node script or Python one-liner; do not source from the internet
- Add `architecture-diagram.svg` and `images-pipeline-diagram.svg` as described in file contracts
- Add `public/resume.pdf` (empty text file renamed)
- Add `public/favicon.svg` as described in file contracts

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] All 15 files exist at correct paths (12 PNG + 2 SVG + 1 PDF)
- [ ] Astro `<Image>` component can reference placeholder PNGs without error
- [ ] `public/resume.pdf` is servable at `/resume.pdf`
- [ ] `public/favicon.svg` appears in browser tab

---

### Scope Contract 3: Base Layout

**UX Slice**
- User opens any page → sees consistent `<head>`, nav, and footer
- Page title updates per route
- OG meta tags present on every page

**Architecture Slice**
- `Base.astro` accepts `title` (required) and `description` (optional, has default) props
- Includes `<ClientRouter />` and `<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" />`
- Includes OG meta tags per the spec in Architecture Contract above
- System font stack in global CSS
- Wraps content in `<main id="main-content">`

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] Create a test page using Base layout → renders with nav and footer
- [ ] Page `<title>` matches prop value
- [ ] OG tags visible in page source (`view-source:`)
- [ ] `<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg">` present in head; favicon visible in browser tab

---

### Scope Contract 4: Navigation Component

**UX Slice**
- User hovers over nav links → visual feedback (underline or color change)
- User clicks nav link → navigates to correct page
- No JavaScript required for hover or navigation

**Architecture Slice**
- `Nav.astro` — pure HTML + CSS, zero JS
- Links: `/about/`, `/projects/`, `/skills/`, `/contact/` — 4 links total
- CSS hover via Tailwind (`hover:underline` or `hover:text-gray-900`)
- No active state logic

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] All 4 nav links visible
- [ ] Hover state visually distinct
- [ ] Each link navigates to correct route (returns 200, not 404)
- [ ] No JS errors in console

---

### Scope Contract 5: Global Styles + Footer + 404 Page

**UX Slice**
- Consistent base styling across all pages
- Footer appears on every page with static content
- Unknown URLs show a custom "Page not found" page instead of Spaceship's default error

**Architecture Slice**
- `src/styles/global.css` — Tailwind directives + body font-family + html smooth scroll
- `Footer.astro` — static `<footer>` with copyright text
- `404.astro` — uses Base layout, title "Page not found", short message, link back to `/`; `export const prerender = true` at top of frontmatter

**Human Verification Checklist**
- [ ] Global styles apply (check font family in DevTools)
- [ ] Footer renders on every placeholder page
- [ ] `astro build` generates `dist/404.html`
- [ ] Visiting a bad URL locally (`astro preview`) shows the custom 404 page, not a server error

## Continuous Verification

- After each scope contract: run `astro dev`, open browser, verify checklist
- After all scopes: navigate between all pages via nav links, confirm consistent layout and no 404s

## Simplicity Guardrails

- Is the nav the simplest possible? (Yes: static links, CSS hover, zero JS)
- Is the layout the simplest possible? (Yes: single layout file, prop-driven title)
- Are placeholders the simplest possible? (Yes: programmatically generated colored rectangles)
- Is the 404 page the simplest possible? (Yes: Base layout + two lines of text + one link)
